"explanation": "Machine learning is a subset of artificial intelligence that focuses on building systems that learn from data [Source: What is Machine Learning?]. It involves algorithms that improve through experience, allowing the system to make predictions or decisions without being explicitly programmed. In other words, machine learning enables computers to learn and adapt based on patterns found in large datasets.",
"example": "For instance, imagine a self-driving car that learns to recognize pedestrians by analyzing video footage of people walking in different environments. Over time, the algorithm improves its accuracy and can make better decisions about when to stop or proceed safely.",
